results.name: Multiplication table A x B computed for polynomials over GF(2), where (A,B) runs as (1,1),(1,2),(2,1),(1,3),(2,2),(3,1),...
comment: Essentially same as A048720 but computed starting from offset one instead of zero. Analogous to A003991. Each n occurs A091220(n) times.
link: A. Karttunen, Scheme-program for computing this sequence.
Index entries for sequences operating on GF(2)[X]-polynomials
xref: a(n) = A048720bi(A091255(n), A091256(n)) because the identity A x B = gcd(A, B) x lcm(A, B) holds also in the polynomial ring GF(2)[X].
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jan 03 2004
